More people have come forward with allegations of rape, sodomy, and abuse against the KwaSizabantu Mission. The CRL Commission is currently investigating the mission for being a cult. Tumelo Mothotoane spoke to a member of the mission, Ruth Combrink. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Allegations of rape, sodomy and abuse against the KwaSizabantu Mission are spread by people, formerly part of the mission, with their own agenda. This is according to Ruth Combrink, daughter of Reverend Erlo Stegen, the man who founded the mission. The Commission for the Promotion and Protection of the Rights of Cultural, Religious and Linguistic Communities (CRL) is currently investigating the mission for being a cult. According to Combrink, the mission takes all the allegations seriously and welcomes the investigation. For more, watch the interview above.